@defigir biggest is being honest w urself:

- postponing 'once i finish this project/pack im done'

- trying to mitigate the habit with stuff like gum or snus

are not quitting, honestly worse

u should possess the mental power to decide u want to quit

and do it. full stop. cold turkey

@defigir mental measures for quitting:

- visualize the deep rooted tendrils nicotine has grown in your brain, and pulling them out

- visualize yourself as a monk on a mountaintop, meditating, controlling your physical desire with mental strength

- tell as many people u quit as possible

@defigir im 6 yrs addicted, 2 years cold turkey with zero relapses

physical measures for quitting:

- chuck the vape/tin/pack somewhere you can see it, but cannot reach it (i threw it onto a roof below my window)

- first 4 days are hell, smoke a lot of weed

- fidget cube

- lollipops
